<subSubSection id="C3234CA1FFE7FF8345B7FC13FE1B86C8" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFE7FF8345B7FC13FE0C8450" blockId="3.[151,550,975,1039]" box="[151,445,1012,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFE7FF8345B7FC13FF668450" box="[151,215,1012,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[189,1401,190,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[172,1416,181,1879]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 A–R. Species of Macropsis, habitus, dorsal and lateral views. A–B, M. campbelli Viraktamath; C–D, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; E–F, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; G–H, M. ganeshai Viraktamath; I–J, M. hamiltoni Viraktamath; K–L, M. irenae Viraktamath; M–N, M. kanakapurensis Viraktamath; O–P, M. karnatakana Viraktamath; Q–R, M. kolarensis Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427921/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Figs 1</figureCitation>
C–D, 3L, 5A–I, 7G.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFE7FF8345B7FBDBFCC28424" blockId="3.[151,1437,1084,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Probably green in life, preserved specimen ochraceous without dark marking on head and thorax. Spot on apex of clavus, series of spots on outer margin of forewing, dark fuscous.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFE7FF8345E7FB63FD578528" blockId="3.[151,1437,1084,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
Head obtusely angled medially. Crown short medially than next to eyes, not raised above level of pronotum. Face convex in profile, rugose, including eyes broader than long. Clypellus constricted in distal 0.66, then expanded with rounded anterior margin, exceeding genal curve. Pronotum convex in profile, about half as long as wide medially, slightly shorter than mesonotum, narrower than head including eyes, rugae obliquely angular, converging on median line, posterior margin slightly concave. Forewing 2.7–2.8 × as long as wide. Basal tergal apodemes of abdomen broad at base, narrowed distally with apices conically rounded (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFE7FF834687FADFFBB3850C" box="[935,1026,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
); sternal (2S) apodemes longer than broad at base, apices more or less truncate (
<figureCitation id="130203AFFFE7FF83475FFABBFD688528" box="[639,729,1372,1398]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,191,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–K. Species of Macropsis. A–F, Female Macropsis krishna sp. nov.: A, Sternites VI and VII, ventral view; B, ovipositor, lateral view; C–D, valvula I, lateral view; E–F, valvula II, lateral view. G–K, basal abdominal apodemes of male, anterior view: G, M. dalhousiensis sp. nov.; H, M. krisha sp. nov., I, M. puttarudriahi sp. nov.; J, M. delhiensis Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; K, M. nigrolineata Viraktamath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4427938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4427938/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFE7FF8345E7FA67FECC8610" blockId="3.[151,1437,1084,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis id="B94DC338FFE7FF8345E7FA67FEDD85C4" box="[199,364,1408,1434]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer dorsal margin angularly expanded medially with round posterior margin; ventral process not extending beyond dorsal margin and apically narrowed and black tipped. Style extended to apex of subgenital plates, upturned near apex and slightly narrowed before rounded and dark pigmented apex. Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme slightly longer than preatrium, shaft broad at base narrowed distally, curved dorsally in basal 0.33, gonopore on ventral margin with apical lateral flanges. Dorsal connective more or less U-shaped with slightly diverging dorsal arms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B861F2AFFE7FF8345E7F9BFFE1B86C8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1084,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis id="B94DC338FFE7FF8345E7F9BFFECC862C" bold="true" box="[199,381,1624,1650]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFE7FF8344E4F9BFFDFA862C" box="[452,587,1624,1651]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" unit="mm" value="4.45" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFE7FF8347B0F9BFFCA6862C" box="[656,791,1624,1650]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="4CC1B2CFFFE7FF83412EF9BFFB24862C" box="[1038,1173,1624,1651]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
